<body>
  <h1>Essential HTML Tags</h1>
  <p>Here are some important HTML tags everyone should know:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code> – Declares the document type.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;html&gt;</code> – The root element of an HTML page.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;head&gt;</code> – Contains meta-information about the page.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;title&gt;</code> – Sets the title of the page (shown in browser tab).</li>
    <li><code>&lt;body&gt;</code> – Contains the visible content of the page.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;</code> – Headings, from largest (<code>h1</code>) to smallest (<code>h6</code>).</li>
    <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code> – Paragraph.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;a&gt;</code> – Anchor/link.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;ul&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> – Lists (unordered, ordered, and list items).</li>
    <li><code>&lt;img&gt;</code> – Embeds an image.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;div&gt;</code> – Generic container for content and layout.</li>
    <li><code>&lt;span&gt;</code> – Inline container for text or elements.</li>
  </ul>

